# WorkerC Task 1: LOA Data Schemas

## 1. Achievements

**Schema (JSON Schema):**
```json
{
  "title": "Achievement",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": { "type": "string" },
    "name": { "type": "string" },
    "description": { "type": "string" },
    "criteria": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "type": { "type": "string" },  // e.g., "kill", "collect", "visit"
        "target": { "type": "string" }, // e.g., NPC ID, item ID
        "quantity": { "type": "integer" }
      },
      "required": ["type", "target"]
    },
    "reward": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "items": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
        "titles": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
      }
    },
    "hidden": { "type": "boolean", "default": false }
  },
  "required": ["id", "name", "criteria"]
}
```

**Example File:**
```json
{
  "id": "first_dragon",
  "name": "First Dragon Slayer",
  "description": "Defeat a dragon for the first time.",
  "criteria": {
    "type": "kill",
    "target": "dragon",
    "quantity": 1
  },
  "reward": {
    "titles": ["Dragon Slayer"]
  }
}
```

**Validation Rules:**
- `id`, `name`, `criteria.type`, `criteria.target` are required.
- `reward` can be empty; optional.
- `criteria.quantity` defaults to 1 if not specified.
- All string fields are non-empty.

